# GATER.NG - Implementation Plan (Next.js, Prisma, PostgreSQL)

## 1. Project Setup

### 1.1 Initialize Project
```bash
# Create Next.js app with TypeScript
npx create-next-app@latest gater.ng --typescript
cd gater.ng

# Install required dependencies
npm install prisma @prisma/client
npm install -D @types/node
npm install @next-auth/prisma-adapter next-auth
npm install @hookform/resolvers zod react-hook-form
npm install zustand
npm install qrcode
npm install @vercel/postgres  # or pg for direct PostgreSQL
npm install @paystack/inline  # Paystack payment integration
```

### 1.2 Initialize Prisma
```bash
npx prisma init --datasource-provider postgresql
```

### 1.3 Environment Setup
Create `.env` file:
```
DATABASE_URL="postgresql://USER:PASSWORD@HOST:PORT/DATABASE?schema=public"
NEXTAUTH_SECRET="your-secret-key"
NEXTAUTH_URL="http://localhost:3000"
PAYSTACK_SECRET_KEY="your_paystack_secret_key"
PAYSTACK_PUBLIC_KEY="your_paystack_public_key"
```

## 2. Database Schema Design (Prisma)

### 2.1 Prisma Schema (`prisma/schema.sql` - actually `schema.prisma`)
```prisma
generator client {
  provider = "prisma-client-js"
}

datasource db {
  provider = "postgresql"
  url      = env("DATABASE_URL")
}

// User Roles
enum Role {
  ADMIN
  ORGANIZER
  ATTENDEE
}

// User Model
model User {
  id            String   @id @default(cuid())
  email         String   @unique
  name          String?
  image         String?
  role          Role     @default(ATTENDEE)
  emailVerified DateTime?
  createdAt     DateTime @default(now())
  updatedAt     DateTime @updatedAt
  accounts      Account[]
  sessions      Session[]
  events        Event[]    @relation("OrganizerEvents")
  orders        Order[]    @relation("BuyerOrders")
  tickets       Ticket[]   @relation("TicketOwner")
  checkIns      CheckIn[]  @relation("Checker")
}

// Authentication (Next-Auth)
model Account {
  id                 String  @id @default(cuid())
  userId             String
  type               String
  provider           String
  providerAccountId  String
  refresh_token      String?   @db.Text
  access_token       String?   @db.Text
  expires_at         Int?
  token_type         String?
  scope              String?
  id_token           String?   @db.Text
  session_state      String?

  user User @relation(fields: [userId], references: [id], onDelete: Cascade)

  @@unique([provider, providerAccountId])
}

model Session {
  id           String   @id @default(cuid())
  sessionToken String   @unique
  userId       String
  expires      DateTime
  user         User     @relation(fields: [userId], references: [id], onDelete: Cascade)
}

model VerificationToken {
  identifier String
  token      String   @unique
  expires    DateTime

  @@unique([identifier, token])
}

// Event Model
model Event {
  id          String   @id @default(cuid())
  title       String
  description String?
  banner      String?  // URL to image stored in cloud/storage
  location    String
  dateTime    DateTime
  isPublished Boolean  @default(false)
  organizerId String
  organizer   User     @relation("OrganizerEvents", fields: [organizerId], references: [id])
  ticketTypes TicketType[] @relation("EventTicketTypes")
  orders      Order[]    @relation("EventOrders")
  createdAt   DateTime @default(now())
  updatedAt   DateTime @updatedAt
}

// Ticket Type Model
model TicketType {
  id          String   @id @default(cuid())
  name        String   // Regular, VIP, Early Bird, etc.
  price       Int      // in smallest currency unit (kobo for NGN)
  quantity    Int
  salesStart  DateTime?
  salesEnd    DateTime?
  eventId     String
  event       Event    @relation("EventTicketTypes", fields: [eventId], references: [id])
  tickets     Ticket[] @relation("TicketTypeTickets")
  createdAt   DateTime @default(now())
  updatedAt   DateTime @updatedAt
}

// Ticket Model (individual ticket)
model Ticket {
  id          String   @id @default(cuid())
  ticketId    String   @unique  // Human-readable ticket code (e.g., GAT-123ABC)
  ticketTypeId String
  ticketType  TicketType @relation("TicketTypeTickets", fields: [ticketTypeId], references: [id])
  ownerId     String?    // Who bought it (null until purchased)
  owner       User?      @relation("TicketOwner", fields: [ownerId], references: [id])
  orderId     String?    // Which order it belongs to
  order       Order?     @relation("OrderTickets", fields: [orderId], references: [id])
  isUsed      Boolean    @default(false)
  usedAt      DateTime?
  usedBy      String?    // Who checked it in (organizer/admin)
  checker     User?      @relation("Checker", fields: [usedBy], references: [id])
  qrCode      String?    // Generated QR data or URL
  createdAt   DateTime @default(now())
  updatedAt   DateTime @updatedAt
}

// Order Model
model Order {
  id           String   @id @default(cuid())
  buyerId      String
  buyer        User     @relation("BuyerOrders", fields: [buyerId], references: [id])
  eventId      String
  event        Event    @relation("EventOrders", fields: [eventId], references: [id])
  status       OrderStatus @default(PENDING)
  amount       Int      // Total in kobo
  paymentRef   String?  // Paystack reference
  paidAt       DateTime?
  createdAt    DateTime @default(now())
  updatedAt    DateTime @updatedAt
  tickets      Ticket[] @relation("OrderTickets")
}

enum OrderStatus {
  PENDING
  PAID
  FAILED
  REFUNDED
}

// Check-in Record (optional, for audit)
model CheckIn {
  id        String   @id @default(cuid())
  ticketId  String
  ticket    Ticket   @relation("CheckIns", fields: [ticketId], references: [id])
  checkedBy String   // Organizer/Admin who did the check-in
  checker   User     @relation("Checker", fields: [checkedBy], references: [id])
  checkedAt DateTime @default(now())
  @@unique([ticketId])
}
```

### 2.2 Apply Migration
```bash
npx prisma migrate dev --name init
npx prisma generate
```

## 3. Next.js Project Structure

```
gater.ng/
├── app/                    # Next.js 13+ app router
│   ├── (auth)/             # Auth routes (login, register, etc.)
│   ├── (organizer)/        # Organizer-protected routes
│   ├── (admin)/            # Admin-protected routes
│   ├── api/                # API routes
│   │   ├── auth/[...nextauth]/route.ts
│   │   ├── events/route.ts
│   │   ├── tickets/route.ts
│   │   ├── orders/route.ts
│   │   ├── paystack/webhook/route.ts
│   │   └── checkin/route.ts
│   ├── dashboard/          # Organizer dashboard
│   ├── events/[id]/        # Individual event page
│   ├── checkout/           # Checkout flow
│   └── layout.tsx
├── components/             # Reusable components
│   ├── ui/                 # Shadcn/ui or custom UI
│   ├── layout/             # Header, Footer, etc.
│   ├── forms/              # Form components
│   └── tickets/            # Ticket-specific components
├── lib/                    # Utility functions
│   ├── prisma.ts           # Prisma client singleton
│   ├── auth.ts             # NextAuth configuration
│   ├── paystack.ts         # Paystack helper functions
│   └── qr.ts               # QR code generation
├── hooks/                  # Custom React hooks
├── prisma/                 # Prisma schema and migrations
├── public/                 # Static assets
├── styles/                 # CSS/Tailwind config
└── types/                  # TypeScript types
```

## 4. Feature Implementation Plan

### Phase 1: Core MVP (Weeks 1-3)

#### 4.1 Authentication & User Management
- [ ] Set up NextAuth with Credentials provider (email/password)
- [ ] Implement registration, login, logout, password reset
- [ ] Role-based access control (Attendee, Organizer, Admin)
- [ ] Optional: Google login, OTP verification (Phase 2)

#### 4.2 Event Management
- [ ] Organizer can create, edit, publish/unpublish, delete events
- [ ] Event form with title, description, banner upload, location, date/time
- [ ] Image upload to local storage (or cloud storage like AWS S3 in Phase 2)
- [ ] Event listing page for attendees (public)

#### 4.3 Ticket Management
- [ ] Organizer can create multiple ticket types per event (Regular, VIP, etc.)
- [ ] Set price, quantity, sales start/end dates for each ticket type
- [ ] Inventory tracking (prevent overselling)

#### 4.4 Payment System (Paystack Integration)
- [ ] Initialize Paystack transaction on checkout
- [ ] Handle Paystack webhook for payment verification
- [ ] Support card, bank transfer, USSD payments
- [ ] Failed payment recovery/retry mechanism

#### 4.5 Order Management
- [ ] Create order on successful payment
- [ ] Track order status (Pending, Paid, Failed)
- [ ] Store buyer info, ticket types, quantities, payment reference

#### 4.6 Digital Ticketing System
- [ ] Generate unique ticket ID (e.g., GAT-XXXXXX)
- [ ] Generate QR code for each ticket (using `qrcode` library)
- [ ] Store QR code as data URL or generate on-demand
- [ ] Ticket includes event details, ticket type, QR code, attendee name

#### 4.7 Ticket Delivery
- [ ] Email ticket delivery (using Nodemailer or SendGrid in Phase 2)
- [ ] Downloadable ticket PDF/PNG
- [ ] Optional: WhatsApp/SMS delivery (Phase 2)

#### 4.8 Event Check-in System
- [ ] Mobile-friendly QR code scanning interface (using browser camera or external scanner)
- [ ] Real-time validation: valid, already used, invalid
- [ ] Mark ticket as used on successful check-in
- [ ] Manual check-in fallback (organizer can search by ticket ID)

#### 4.9 Organizer Dashboard
- [ ] Overview of events with sales metrics
- [ ] Ticket sales tracking per event
- [ ] Revenue analytics (total revenue, pending payments)
- [ ] Attendee list with filtering/search
- [ ] Export attendee list as CSV

#### 4.10 Public Event Discovery
- [ ] Browse upcoming events (published events only)
- [ ] Search events by title/location
- [ ] Filter by date (upcoming, past)
- [ ] Event page showing details, ticket options, purchase button

### Phase 2: Enhancements (Weeks 4-6)

#### 4.11 Admin Panel
- [ ] View all users, events, transactions
- [ ] Monitor disputes, issue refunds
- [ ] System settings management

#### 4.12 Security & Fraud Prevention
- [ ] Ensure unique QR per ticket, one-time validation
- [ ] Payment verification via webhook (already in Phase 1)
- [ ] Rate limiting on API endpoints
- [ ] Input sanitization and validation

#### 4.13 System Notifications
- [ ] Ticket purchase success email/SMS
- [ ] Event reminder emails (optional)
- [ ] Payment failure notifications

#### 4.14 File & Media Management
- [ ] Efficient image storage and serving (optimize uploads, use CDN)
- [ ] Consider integrating with Cloudinary/AWS S3

#### 4.15 Analytics (Basic)
- [ ] Sales trends (daily/weekly/monthly)
- [ ] Ticket performance by type
- [ ] Attendance rate calculation (checked-in vs. total sold)

