## 6. Technical Considerations

### 6.1 Database
- Use PostgreSQL for relational data and scalability
- Index frequently queried fields (eventId, ticketId, ownerId, status)
- Consider partitioning for high-volume ticket tables if needed

### 6.2 Authentication
- NextAuth with JWT or database sessions
- Secure password hashing (bcrypt)
- Role-based middleware for route protection

### 6.3 Paystack Integration
- Use Paystack's inline JavaScript or SDK for frontend
- Verify webhook signatures for security
- Handle idempotency in webhook processing

### 6.4 QR Code Generation
- Generate QR codes as SVGs or PNGs on-demand
- Consider caching generated QRs to reduce computation
- Use libraries like `qrcode` or `qr-code-styling` for custom designs

### 6.5 Image Handling
- Store images in public/uploads or use external storage (Cloudinary/S3)
- Optimize images on upload (resize, compress)
- Implement lazy loading for event banners

### 6.6 State Management
- Use React Query/SWR for server state
- Use Zustand or Context API for client state (cart, user info)
- Avoid prop drilling with proper context usage

### 6.7 Error Handling & Logging
- Implement error boundaries in React
- Log errors to external service (Sentry, LogRocket) in production
- Validate all API inputs with Zod

### 6.8 Performance
- Implement pagination for large lists (events, attendees, orders)
- Use incremental static regeneration (ISR) for public event pages
- Optimize database queries with Prisma's select/include

### 6.9 Security
- Use helmet.js or equivalent for security headers
- Sanitize user inputs to prevent XSS
- Implement CSRF protection for forms
- Use environment variables for secrets
- Regular dependency updates

## 7. Optional Integrations (Future Phases)
